In the 2020 census, there were 340 people, 41 families, and 119 housing units. The racial demographics of the CDP was 38.5% [[White Americans|White]], 1.4% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0.2% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 50% from some other race, and 9.7% from two or more races. 63.2% of the population had [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] ancestry. 15.1% of the population speaks [[Spanish language|Spanish]] at home.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Chelan_Falls_CDP,_Washington?g=160XX00US5311685#race-and-ethnicity |access-date=2024-03-11 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>
